Angular
  -javascript binding framework

--MVVM - angular implements
  M-Model
  V-View
  VM-View Model

  MVW - Model View Whatever

--SPA (Single Page Application)

--Router
  - listens to the events
  -DOM (Document Object Model) & HTML Rendering is done by router
  -Mapping the templates
  -HTML rendering happens at the client side
  -Dynamic Rendering
  -Not appropriate for search engines

--Typescript
  -Strongly typed language
  -Superset of javascript
  -Traspiling - .ts -> .js

--ng serve - Browser Sync (watch for the changes in your file)

--Angular Bootstraping
  -script inclusions were done as part of build process
  -main.ts -> bootstrap -> AppModule --> @NgModule (bootStrap:[AppComponent])

--Directives
  Change the behaviour of HTML DOM
  -Structural Directive
  -Attribute Directive
  -Component Directive

  --Structural Directive
    change the DOM layout by adding and removing elements
  --Attribute Directive
    change the appearance and behaviour of HTML element (true visible/false invisible)
  --Component Directive
    Directives with templates, Its like user control (own UI code)

   ng-content -- in-built directive

--component
  Mediator for view and Model where you write your binding code


--Data Binding
  It defines how view and component communicate with each other
  -Expression/Interpolation binding
  -Property binding
  -Event binding
  -Two-way binding

  --Expression/Interpolation binding
    Data flows from comp -> view
    {{emp.fName}}
  --Property binding
    [], comp -> view, eg: textbox
    Assigns a component property to html element attribute/dom props
    [ngModel] -> change of property


--Create a componnet using angular cli
  -ng generate component other
  -ng g c another --flat
  -ng g c onemore --flat --it --is (it -> inline template, is -> inline style)


